Quiz: assignment

viewof q1 = Inputs.radio(
  ["= =", "&lt;-", "==", "-&gt;&gt;"],
  { label: "Which operator assigns a value to an object in R?" }
);
html`${q1 == null ? "" : q1 === "&lt;-" ? "&lt;strong&gt;Correct.&lt;/strong&gt; R assigns with &lt;code&gt;&lt;-&lt;/code&gt; (Alt/Option and minus)." : "&lt;em&gt;Not quite.&lt;/em&gt; R's assignment arrow points left."}`

Quiz: install vs load

viewof q2 = Inputs.radio(
  ["Installs a package from the internet", "Loads an installed package for use", "Deletes a package", "Updates R"],
  { label: "What does library(tidyverse) do?" }
);
html`${q2 == null ? "" : q2 === "Loads an installed package for use" ? "&lt;strong&gt;Correct.&lt;/strong&gt; install.packages() downloads once; library() loads it each session." : "&lt;em&gt;Try again.&lt;/em&gt; Downloading the package is a separate step."}`

